Heinrich I (W230) had decided that his sons should rule jointly after his death.

Heinrich II (W260) ruled 1322-1351, Ernest II (W270) ruled 1322-1361, William II (W280) ruled 1322-1360, and Johann II (281) ruled 1322-1325.

Ernst lived for the longest time, and his sons (W271 + 272) inherited the ruling power of Grubenhagen. However, John III (W272) abdicated 1364 to join the clergy, and Albert III (W271) became sole ruler from 1364 to 1383.

