Braunschweig-Grubenhagen is divided

Heinrich V (W274) divided the duchy in 1440 and gave a part (Part 2) to his brother Albrecht V (W275).

When Heinrich died in 1464 Albrecht became regent for Heinrich's son Heinrich VI (W276). However, Heinrich VI died without descendants, and the land went to Albrecht V's line. Unfortunately (or fortunately) only one of Albert's sons, Philip (W277) was still alive, and he reunited Grubenhagen in 1526.

